Stitch follows the story of grieving parents Marsden (Edward Furlong) and Serafina (Shawna Waldron) 
as they cope with the loss of their young daughter. 
At the height of their desperation, they turn to their best friends Pirino (Laurence Mason) 
and Colline (Shirly Brener) for healing advice. 
Their well-meaning friends lead them into the deep desert for a week-end ritual meant to burn away emotional baggage. 
Unfortunately, the amateur ritual goes awry and cosmic forces are unleashed.
